Because we have't had read/write editing capabilty, we have
maintained the GEDCOM under RISCOS !Family all these years,
and the file headers reflect this. Now we can do the work in
X!Family, we can updtae these (and the program should save
files with the new headers, rather than me just changing the
file...)

0 HEAD
1 SOUR !Family_for_RISC_OS
2 VERS 2.2.7 20170913
1 GEDC
2 VERS 5.3
2 FORM LINEAGE-LINKED
2 LANG English
1 LANG English
1 SUBM @A1@
1 SCHEMA
2 INDI
3 _NINO
4 LABL NATIONAL_INSURANCE_NUMBER
4 DEFN United Kingdom National Insurance Number
4 ISA IDNO
1 SCHEMA
2 INDI
3 _NHSNO
4 LABL NATIONAL_HEALTH_NUMBER
4 DEFN United Kingdom National Health Service Number
4 ISA IDNO

An obvious issue is that we use a mix of VERS 5.3 and VERS 5.5
Do we believe there is any reason not to mention both ?

I have never specified a language. Even the 5.5 spec. doesn't
actually say how to specify UTF-8... 5.5.1 does

1 CHAR UTF-8

The 1 SCHEMA construct was taken out of 5.5, which is a pity,
as we have no other formal way of keeping these national ID
numbers. Although, having said that, 5.5.1 includes the IDNO
tag for "National ID number" which can have a subordinate
structure the most useful of which would be +1 TYPE, eg.
for dad:

1 IDNO TH 91 11 70 D
2 TYPE UK National Insurance Number
1 IDNO KOMZ 30/3
2 UK National Health Service Number

those should have date ranges - NHS numbers were originally Identity Card
numbers (so issued c 1939), then were retained for NHS use, then all got
changed.

