Whilst we're here, we can note down how we are supposed to support
some features.



Adoption

0 @I1@ INDI
1 FAMC @F1@
1 FAMC @F2@
2 PEDI Adopted
1 ADOP
2 FAMC @F2@
2 DATE ...

this will break both Family and X!Family which do not expect
to see a FAMC twice at the top level. Elsewhere in the spec.
it looks as though the first (top-level) FAMC for the adoptive
partnership is optional. The trouble with that is that we use
the top-level one to show the tree graphically.

There is an additional bit of structure to show which partner
adopted (HUSB/WIFE/BOTH) but again, this fails to cope with
a same-sex civil partnership ...

Military, police or other service rank

TITL is supposed for be for "Nobility title", not rank.
rank is supposed to go after the NAME as a +1

both ranks and titles have effective dates, and higher rank, additional titles
etc. should be documented.

